    "attributes": {
        "action": "Government to Give More Power to SFO to Investigate Insurance Companies",
        "additional_details": "The SFO to be given unlimited powers to gain access to all computer/manual records from all parties & look into:\r\n\u2022\tInsurance companies & other parties involved including experts \r\n\u2022\tHow customers are pressurised to accept terms/sign agreements.\r\n\u2022\tThe instructions given to experts \r\n\u2022\tThe use of unidentified experts \r\n\u2022\tCustomers being forced to take a lesser payment so that the insurers can discharge their responsibility\r\n\u2022\tWhat happens to the monies allocated for the claim\r\n\r\nSFO to take appropriate action",
        "background": "Currently the Financial Ombudsman have no power to investigate complex complaints involving more than one party particularly when insurance claims have been failed due to the incorrect input by several parties. A new law is vital to enable the Serious Fraud Office to investigate all parties involved",
